---
title: Definition of Apparatus
tags:
  - Apparatus
---
A relational network of practices, bodies of knowledge, measures, and institutions that aim to manage, control, orient, structure, and align the behaviors, gestures, and thoughts of human beings, in direct response to a particular need. In other words, an apparatus is a network of measures that organize a multitude of problematized inputs into a coherent, self-correcting system.
